comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:55:08.230Z",codex-root,Use top-level imports and direct logic; do not add one-use wrapper helpers or dynamic imports.
  "2026-07-23T04:58:43.073Z",codex-root,"Focused command,WebSocket regression,help-surface,typecheck,lint,and file-size gates pass. The command accepts singular CLI/file fields and emits plural wire keys proven by live 2026.4.4 and current Core source."
  "2026-07-23T05:07:41.820Z",codex-root,The public command accepts singular CLI terminology but sends the plural triggers conditions actions contract required by current Core. Empty action arrays are intentionally valid and ideal for non-mutating live acceptance.
  "2026-07-23T05:15:20.367Z",codex-root,"Acceptance is complete: seven command tests pass; compiled live E2E validates an empty actions array without mutation; six formats were decoded or structurally checked; aggregate release verification passed with 1208 pre-final tests and 100 percent across all four metrics."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:55:08.230Z",codex-root,"Live evidence records only validation booleans and server version,never submitted private definitions or raw responses."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:55:08.230Z",codex-root,Stable CLI option names can normalize wire-contract inconsistencies without removing the raw ws call escape hatch.
